GRWM: Festive glam✨
Hair strengthening mask
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
✨Ingredients and method:
.
Scrap out the pulp of one aloe vera leaf and add an egg to it along with some tbsps of coconut oil. 
Add this concoction to the mixer, you’ll obtain a juice like consistency. 
Apply this to your scalp and ends thoroughly and wash off after an hour. 
.
✨Benefits:
.
1. Aloe vera:
.
✅Promotes hair growth 
✅Strengthens and repairs hair
✅Treats itchy scalp
✅Deep cleans oily hair
.
2. Egg:
.
✅Damage resistant 
✅Superfood for your hair
✅Protein rich
✅Gives a shine
.
3. Coconut oil:
.
✅Curbs hairfall
✅Nourishes scalp
✅Reduces frizz
✅Fights bacteria
.
Using @parachute_advansed Ayurvedic hot coconut oil.
. 
🚫:Make sure you do a patch test before you apply this hair mask, incase you’re allergic to any of the ingredients. 
Wear an old t-shirt and lay down newspapers to avoid mess.
.
💁🏻‍♀️: If you happen to try this mask, don’t forget to tag @friesandvogue in your stories/posts.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Skin purifying facemask
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
.
I make sure to apply this mask atleast once in a month, my skin feels rejuvenated and looks glowing.
.
✨Ingredients:
.
•Amla powder @dagdu_teli 
 (Indian gooseberry powder)
•Multani mitti @dagdu_teli 
(Fuller’s earth)
•Gulab jal. @alphavedicorp 
(Rose water)
.
✨Mix everything and apply on your face, keep it until it semidries. (7-10 mins)
Rinse it and pat dry. 
Spray rose water or your favourite toner
Apply moisturiser and SPF if it’s daytime.
.
If you have a normal to dry skin type add raw milk instead of rose water or avoid multani mitti.
.
✨Amla powder:
.
•Provides blood circulation 
•Treats hyper pigmentation
•Has anti-ageing properties 
•Removes dead skin 
•Purifies your skin
.
✨Multani mitti:
.
•Fights acne and pimples
•Removes excess sebum and oil
•Reduces inflammation 
•Treats tanning and pigmentation
•Treats sunburns
.
✨Rose water:
.
•Reduces skin redness
•Anti microbial 
•Anti inflammatory 
•Tones and balances ph 
.
⚠️ Make sure you do a patch test on your jawline or behind your ear incase you’re allergic to any of the ingredients. 
.
If you try out this mask, do tag @friesandvogue in your stories, I ll repost them.
.

latestIgtvVideos.title: Reviewing kayos tea ☕️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
@kayosherbals tea for healthy hair and glowing skin. 
Honestly, I am not a person who will opt for herbal tea over masala chai, but when @kayosnaturals sent this to me, I am hooked ever since.I haven’t sipped masala chai in weeks now. 
.
This tea benefits you with healthy hair and glowing skin. 
It helps detoxify your body, acts as a DHT blocker and promotes melanin.
.
It doesn’t tastes weird, so basically you can keep sipping it. 
You can also reuse the tea leaves twice. You just have to allow 30 extra seconds steeping time for reuse.
Herbal things take time to show results so you need to be patient and enjoy meanwhile.
.
If you wish to buy this product, you can find link in @kayosnaturals bio and @amazondotin 
.
